  "texts": [
    "This dialogue sheds light on the material bodily conditions from which subjectivity emerges and can indeed reinforce some readings of Foucault (Oksala 2005).",
    "In summary, the motivation is a social-technological question of value alignment and AI responsibility; the end goal is a malleable, self-conducting Foucauldian subject; the means is a phenomenological-Foucauldian exploration of the emergence of subjectivity.",
    "The work is structured in two parts.",
    "In the first part, I identify the prevailing strands of critique (Sect. 2) and the material and ideological preconditions from which generative AI emerged (Sect.",
    "I also look briefly at the technical workings of ChatGPT to illustrate the conditions of its speech production (Sect. 4), observing that ChatGPT enacts fixed ontologies, epistemologies and axiologies (Sect."
  ]
}